This paper discusses the impact of noise on neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also considers the optimization of inference algorithm parameters, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of statistical properties of internal noise to optimize the algorithm is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the threshold phenomenon, which is a topic in the field of complex systems and networks (cs.SI).
